                <h2>Nutritional Needs for Dogs</h2>
                <p>Ensuring a balanced diet is essential for your dog's health:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Protein:</strong> Dogs require high-quality protein sources like meat, fish, and eggs for muscle development and overall health.</li>
                    <li><strong>Carbohydrates:</strong> Incorporate grains and vegetables for energy and digestive health.</li>
                    <li><strong>Fats:</strong> Provide essential fatty acids from sources like fish oil and flaxseed for a healthy coat and skin.</li>
                    <li><strong>Vitamins and Minerals:</strong> Ensure a balanced intake of vitamins and minerals through a complete commercial dog food or appropriate supplements.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Avoid feeding dogs human foods that are toxic to them, such as chocolate, grapes, and onions.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Environmental Needs -->
        <section class="info-section">
            <div class="info-container">
                <h2>Ideal Environment for Dogs</h2>
                <p>Creating a comfortable and safe environment is crucial for dogs:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Sleeping Area:</strong> Provide a clean, comfortable, and cozy bed in a quiet area of your home.</li>
                    <li><strong>Outdoor Space:</strong> Ensure access to a secure, fenced area where they can play and exercise.</li>
                    <li><strong>Temperature:</strong> Maintain a suitable indoor temperature to keep them comfortable, avoiding extreme heat or cold.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Regularly clean their living area and ensure it’s free from hazards.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Common Diseases and Prevention -->
        <section class="info-section">
            <div class="info-container">
                <h2>Common Health Issues and Prevention</h2>
                <p>Being aware of common health issues helps in effective prevention:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Fleas and Ticks:</strong> Use regular preventive treatments and check your dog for parasites frequently.</li>
                    <li><strong>Ear Infections:</strong> Clean their ears regularly and monitor for signs of infection such as itching or discharge.</li>
                    <li><strong>Obesity:</strong> Maintain a healthy diet and exercise routine to prevent weight-related issues.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Regular vet visits and vaccinations are essential for overall health and disease prevention.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Health Maintenance and Best Practices -->
        <section class="info-section">
